# Epsilon Quant Research — line-ending normalization (cross-platform).
# Mac collaborator (justin) uses LF; Windows collaborator (alvaro) emits CRLF.
# Goal: store LF in the repo (index) AND check out LF on every platform, so
# merges never produce whitespace-only (CRLF) conflicts.
# Rationale + one-time history fix + per-platform git config: brain/MERGE_PROTOCOL.md § 6.

# --- Default: treat everything as text, normalize to LF in repo AND working tree ---
# eol=lf forces LF in the working tree even on Windows, so a re-save can't flip to CRLF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# --- Binary / asset types: never EOL-convert, never line-diff (all hold NUL bytes) ---
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.webp  binary
*.ico   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.odt   binary
*.docx  binary
*.xlsx  binary
*.pptx  binary
*.pkl   binary
*.pickle binary
*.parquet binary
*.duckdb binary
*.zip   binary
*.gz    binary
*.xz    binary
*.so    binary
*.dylib binary

# --- Notebooks: preserve existing nbstripout + ipynb-diff behavior.
# -text guarantees no EOL coercion while keeping the filter and diff driver intact.
*.ipynb -text filter=nbstripout diff=ipynb
*.zpln  -text filter=nbstripout
